WEBVTT

00:01.466 --> 00:04.666
No, no, no.
Don't touch that dial.

00:04.733 --> 00:07.633
Here's what's on my mind,
tonight.

00:10.533 --> 00:14.300
Tony Dow and Sandahl Bergman
are recovering cannibals.

00:14.366 --> 00:18.866
I promise to never again
raise my fork

00:18.933 --> 00:20.966
against my fellowmen.

00:21.033 --> 00:23.300
Who just fell off the wagon.

00:23.366 --> 00:25.600
Bet you can't
take just one bite.

00:25.666 --> 00:28.966
But this time, they bit off
more than they can chew

00:29.033 --> 00:31.033
on "Freddy's Nightmares."

00:31.100 --> 00:35.300
Where they only meet
to eat each other.

00:55.033 --> 00:57.500
You are in Springwood now.

00:57.566 --> 00:59.666
And you are all mine.

01:23.433 --> 01:24.733
'Here's the dip everyone.'

01:24.800 --> 01:26.266
'Oh, great. Thanks.'

01:26.333 --> 01:27.300
'Over here.'

01:27.366 --> 01:29.100
Hi, Tim.
You're just in time.

01:29.166 --> 01:31.366
Uh, uh, I think there's
a spot in the back.

01:32.866 --> 01:34.433
- 'Here, there's room here.'
- Watch it.

01:34.500 --> 01:35.700
- 'Oh, hey.'
- 'Hi.'

01:40.366 --> 01:42.033
Hello, and welcome.

01:42.100 --> 01:44.066
My name is Johnny and..

01:44.133 --> 01:45.100
...I'm a cannibal.

01:45.166 --> 01:46.966
Hi, Johnny.

01:48.266 --> 01:50.600
But, uh, human flesh
has not passed my lips

01:50.666 --> 01:52.066
for the past three months now.

01:52.133 --> 01:54.033
- 'Alright.'
- 'Yay!'

01:54.100 --> 01:55.600
And that's what
we're all about here.

01:55.666 --> 01:57.233
Getting by day to day.

01:57.300 --> 02:00.333
Getting by without taking
a bite of that arm or leg.

02:00.400 --> 02:03.333
And leaving our neighbors,
just as we found them. Whole.

02:04.733 --> 02:05.666
Now, um..

02:08.900 --> 02:10.533
Who took my seat?

02:10.600 --> 02:12.666
Mary, Mary Beth,
just sit down anywhere.

02:12.733 --> 02:14.600
But this is a new dress.

02:14.666 --> 02:17.233
- Mary Beth.
- God, how rude.

02:17.300 --> 02:18.966
Uh, thank you.

02:19.033 --> 02:21.566
You know, we are all here
for each other.

02:21.633 --> 02:24.200
Uh, for example, um,
just last week.

02:24.266 --> 02:27.500
Young Brian here was tempted
by his neighbors wife.

02:27.566 --> 02:29.866
He had visions of,
uh, milky white thighs

02:29.933 --> 02:31.666
and succulent breasts

02:31.733 --> 02:33.700
in a potato and leek stew.

02:33.766 --> 02:35.633
And he was weakening.

02:35.700 --> 02:37.533
But before he faltered,
he called David.

02:37.600 --> 02:39.400
And David was there for him.

02:39.466 --> 02:40.866
- David.
- Yeah.

02:43.833 --> 02:47.666
Most of you know me,
I'm Ginger and I'm a cannibal.

02:47.733 --> 02:49.900
Hi, Ginger.

02:49.966 --> 02:52.533
But it was out of survival
that I turned to human flesh.

02:52.600 --> 02:53.766
Johnny, Mary Beth and I

02:53.833 --> 02:55.766
were trapped out here
in the mountains.

02:55.833 --> 02:59.133
Our first mortal meals
were already dead.

02:59.200 --> 03:02.766
They were victims of the same
plane crash that stranded us.

03:02.833 --> 03:05.500
But then, we found
we liked it..

03:05.566 --> 03:07.066
...especially with
the right sauce.

03:07.133 --> 03:08.333
Hmm.

03:08.400 --> 03:09.966
We knew that we were addicted

03:10.033 --> 03:12.200
when normal food seemed bland

03:12.266 --> 03:14.700
and we had cravings
for the well formed man

03:14.766 --> 03:16.866
which is the most
natural of foods.

03:16.933 --> 03:19.466
But we live in
a junk food society

03:19.533 --> 03:22.966
so we must deal with
the ugly face of prejudice.

03:23.033 --> 03:25.600
And you know, I, uh, I had
to step down as a president

03:25.666 --> 03:28.833
of my corporation, because
the rumor started to spread.

03:28.900 --> 03:30.800
And Ginger here, had to move
out into this trailer

03:30.866 --> 03:34.033
out in the woods because,
uh, she was being persecuted.

03:34.100 --> 03:37.933
And just last week, Mary Beth
had her credit cards revoked.

03:38.000 --> 03:40.633
- Oh!
- Those heartless bastards.

03:40.700 --> 03:43.600
But to live in peace,
we must, uh, once again

03:43.666 --> 03:45.166
be like the others.

03:45.233 --> 03:46.833
So that is why..

03:48.600 --> 03:53.000
I promise to never again
raise my fork

03:53.066 --> 03:55.200
against my fellowman.

03:56.433 --> 03:57.500
- Alright.
- Yeah!

03:59.633 --> 04:01.900
Hey, listen. Thank you,
thank you very much for coming.

04:01.966 --> 04:03.500
Oh, and the, uh,
vegetable recipe

04:03.566 --> 04:04.600
is available on the way out.

04:04.666 --> 04:05.766
- 'Oh, yeah.'
- 'Yeah.'

04:05.833 --> 04:07.400
'I made copies for everyone.'

04:14.133 --> 04:15.900
- Take care.
- Bye.

04:15.966 --> 04:18.300
Bye-bye, guys.
Drive carefully.

04:31.900 --> 04:33.400
I've been thinking
about you, Ginger.

04:33.466 --> 04:35.400
A lot.

04:35.466 --> 04:37.400
I haven't been
with another woman, since you.

04:38.566 --> 04:40.033
What about Mary Beth?

04:41.166 --> 04:42.400
She took a vow of chastity

04:42.466 --> 04:44.000
when they revoked
her credit cards.

04:47.433 --> 04:48.733
How about you?

04:48.800 --> 04:53.000
Outside of eating them, yours
were the last arms that I felt.

05:00.666 --> 05:03.133
Not touching you is harder
than staying on the wagon and..

05:03.200 --> 05:05.433
...not tearing flesh
with my teeth.

05:05.500 --> 05:08.066
Then why torture yourself?

05:28.300 --> 05:29.500
- Hey.
- What?

05:29.566 --> 05:31.733
Help me. You gotta hide me.

05:31.800 --> 05:33.333
They're out there
and they're gonna find me.

05:33.400 --> 05:34.333
- Who?
- What?

05:34.400 --> 05:35.333
- Where?
- Why?

05:35.400 --> 05:36.933
How did you get in here?

05:37.000 --> 05:39.100
Oh, oh, it's too late.

05:40.666 --> 05:41.900
Ah!

05:53.633 --> 05:55.233
You are what you eat, babe.

05:55.300 --> 05:57.333
So..

05:57.400 --> 06:00.033
...get this recipe right.

06:00.100 --> 06:01.933
Well, you take your eggs

06:02.000 --> 06:03.600
uh, one, uh, two, uh, three.

06:03.666 --> 06:06.000
You get some flour. Hmm.

06:06.066 --> 06:07.266
A little sugar.

06:08.966 --> 06:11.066
Don't forget the butter. Yah!

06:11.133 --> 06:13.433
And you got your chopped meat.

06:15.366 --> 06:16.833
Where's my chopped meat?

06:18.400 --> 06:22.000
I said chopped meat, guys.

06:22.066 --> 06:25.333
Ah, don't worry.
Uh, I can take care of that.

06:26.866 --> 06:29.866
Wait till you see
how I serve up this guy.

06:46.533 --> 06:48.966
Bet you can't
take just one bite.

06:49.033 --> 06:50.500
You flesh addict!

06:51.266 --> 06:53.933
That's cheating.

06:54.000 --> 06:55.633
Oh, you,
you don't know how tired I'm

06:55.700 --> 06:58.400
of carrot sticks, sprouts
and-and quiche.

06:59.666 --> 07:01.833
No mas. No mas.

07:03.300 --> 07:04.833
N-no mas.

07:20.466 --> 07:21.833
We were hungry.

07:21.900 --> 07:23.233
We both had a nightmare.

07:23.300 --> 07:24.733
Me too.

07:27.066 --> 07:28.733
We're all thinking
the same thing.

07:28.800 --> 07:31.233
But we're not
going to do it.

07:31.300 --> 07:33.700
I was thinking casserole.

07:33.766 --> 07:36.200
Or a souffle.

07:36.266 --> 07:38.200
Firm, yet tender.

07:39.400 --> 07:40.966
What do you think
he was talking about?

07:41.033 --> 07:42.566
'Somebody's after him.'

07:42.633 --> 07:44.633
Maybe he did
something terrible.

07:44.700 --> 07:46.166
Maybe he's just
an innocent man.

07:46.233 --> 07:47.833
Men are never innocent.

07:47.900 --> 07:50.266
Which brings me to what
you were doing earlier tonight

07:50.333 --> 07:51.833
with your pants off.

08:08.066 --> 08:10.266
Oh, my God!
We killed him.

08:10.333 --> 08:13.000
- He was gonna kill, Johnny.
- What are we gonna do?

08:13.066 --> 08:14.600
He said people were looking
for him.

08:14.666 --> 08:16.800
If we leave him like this,
we're all gonna go to jail.

08:16.866 --> 08:19.100
They have very rough
toilet paper in prison.

08:19.166 --> 08:20.166
We gotta get rid of the body.

08:20.233 --> 08:21.533
How?

08:23.600 --> 08:25.366
Set the table.

08:25.433 --> 08:27.833
Your liver pate was really
excellent, Mary Beth.

08:27.900 --> 08:30.566
Fortunately,
he wasn't a drinker.

08:30.633 --> 08:32.966
You know,
we forgot to say grace.

08:33.033 --> 08:35.000
It's the least we could do.

08:36.633 --> 08:38.233
We thank you for this feast.

08:38.300 --> 08:39.400
We know that you forgive us

08:39.466 --> 08:40.900
for if you did not
want us to eat

08:40.966 --> 08:42.633
you would not have
made us of meat.

08:42.700 --> 08:44.633
- 'Amen.'
- Amen.

08:46.966 --> 08:49.666
This won't look good at the next
cannibals anonymous meeting.

08:49.733 --> 08:51.966
Which is why,
we won't tell anyone.

08:52.033 --> 08:54.100
Gee, Mary Beth, get with
the program, will you?

08:54.166 --> 08:55.833
You just ate a guy.

08:55.900 --> 08:56.866
We're not gonna go around
telling everybody

08:56.933 --> 08:57.866
that we're sorry.

08:57.933 --> 08:59.033
What're we gonna say
when people

08:59.100 --> 09:00.300
come around
asking questions?

09:00.366 --> 09:02.500
Nothing, we haven't
seen anybody.

09:02.566 --> 09:04.300
We'll burn his clothes
in the morning.

09:04.366 --> 09:05.800
Did you freeze,
some of that pate?

09:05.866 --> 09:07.133
Yes.

09:09.466 --> 09:12.900
And the leftover tongue
is for sandwiches tomorrow.

09:14.333 --> 09:16.900
Oh. Stealers just don't make the
playoffs if they win on Sunday.

09:23.833 --> 09:25.033
Hey, what are you doing?

09:25.100 --> 09:26.433
Oh, my God!

09:26.500 --> 09:27.933
This is the man we just ate.

09:28.000 --> 09:30.866
- Where?
- Right here, on the front page.

09:30.933 --> 09:33.100
What does it say?

09:33.166 --> 09:35.500
"Garrett Evan has escaped
from an isolated government lab

09:35.566 --> 09:37.800
"yesterday where
he was undergoing tests.

09:37.866 --> 09:39.366
Anyone seen
this man should contact.."

09:39.433 --> 09:41.133
Blah, blah, blah..
"Immediately.

09:41.200 --> 09:42.866
"Under no circumstances
should you attempt to

09:42.933 --> 09:44.600
"approach him or touch him.

09:44.666 --> 09:47.966
"Garrett Evans is believed to be
carrying a deadly yet unknown

09:48.033 --> 09:50.666
virus possibly
highly contagious."

09:59.733 --> 10:02.266
Now remember, he just came by
for directions and then he left.

10:02.333 --> 10:04.633
I just dumped all
of the left overs.

10:04.700 --> 10:07.566
That was some of my best
chopped liver pate.

10:07.633 --> 10:09.600
Hello, uh..

10:11.033 --> 10:12.633
Yes.

10:12.700 --> 10:14.633
The article in the paper.

10:15.900 --> 10:17.600
'Yes, we think so.'

10:17.666 --> 10:19.500
- We've got a live one.
- 'Put it on the scrambler.'

10:19.566 --> 10:20.700
Trace that call.

10:20.766 --> 10:22.066
Don't say anything that
might frighten them.

10:22.133 --> 10:23.900
- Stay calm.
- Anything else?

10:23.966 --> 10:26.433
For God's sake,
don't hang up on them.

10:26.500 --> 10:28.066
- What's going on?
- I'm on hold.

10:28.133 --> 10:30.766
Hold, we're standing here, dying
rotting from the inside out

10:30.833 --> 10:33.333
from some stupid disease
and you put us on hold?

10:35.166 --> 10:37.466
Listen, you
flea brained moron.

10:37.533 --> 10:39.200
How dare you treat
tax paying citizens..

10:39.266 --> 10:41.033
What?

10:41.100 --> 10:44.266
My name?
Y-you wanna know my name?

10:44.333 --> 10:46.233
Hold on.

10:46.300 --> 10:48.233
I think you should
talk to them.

10:49.233 --> 10:51.333
Hello.

10:51.400 --> 10:53.466
Yes.

10:53.533 --> 10:55.500
No, she's usually like that.

10:57.533 --> 10:59.433
Just a minute.

10:59.500 --> 11:01.000
Have you noticed any
recent sweating problem?

11:01.066 --> 11:03.500
Oh, my God! Is that
one of the symptoms?

11:03.566 --> 11:05.766
I'm gonna turn into drooling
sniveling vegetables?

11:05.833 --> 11:07.100
Get a grip, Mary Beth.

11:07.166 --> 11:09.700
She says no.

11:09.766 --> 11:11.900
Uh, yeah, we're pretty sure.

11:13.733 --> 11:16.833
He just came by to ask
directions. He seemed lost.

11:18.733 --> 11:20.700
And then, uh..

11:20.766 --> 11:21.933
He left, he left.

11:22.000 --> 11:23.833
He left.

11:23.900 --> 11:26.333
Did you eat anything
he might have touched?

11:29.333 --> 11:31.400
They...they wanna know

11:31.466 --> 11:33.400
if we ate anything
that he might've touched.

11:35.233 --> 11:36.700
A-a-ah!

11:38.800 --> 11:40.300
We may have.

11:41.900 --> 11:43.366
Yes.

11:43.433 --> 11:44.733
I understand.

11:46.166 --> 11:48.300
Ginger Morgan.

11:48.366 --> 11:49.633
Springwood trailer park, uh

11:49.700 --> 11:51.833
I'm at the back,
at the edge of the forest.

11:53.500 --> 11:54.500
Yes.

11:55.566 --> 11:56.833
Okay.

11:58.166 --> 11:59.933
Could you please, hurry?

12:01.633 --> 12:04.400
They're sending somebody over.

12:04.466 --> 12:06.333
What's going to happen to us?

12:06.400 --> 12:09.333
All they know now, is that
it causes personality changes.

12:16.600 --> 12:18.533
What's that noise?

12:20.266 --> 12:23.566
Mary Beth is the only one
that caught the virus.

12:23.633 --> 12:26.533
Is her personality
change permanent?

12:26.600 --> 12:28.533
I'm afraid so,
there is no known cure.

12:30.033 --> 12:32.300
She is now a compulsive cleaner.

12:32.366 --> 12:33.500
Mostly toilets.

12:33.566 --> 12:35.533
Actually she's, uh,
pretty good, pretty cheap.

12:42.800 --> 12:44.066
Mary Beth, what is it?

12:44.133 --> 12:46.333
You wouldn't let me turn into
a cleaning woman, would you?

12:46.400 --> 12:48.100
You'd kill me first,
won't you?

12:48.166 --> 12:49.466
Mary Beth,
I'm not going to kill you

12:49.533 --> 12:50.966
if you turn
into a cleaning woman.

12:51.033 --> 12:53.566
Huh, that-that virus,
if it turns into anything.

12:53.633 --> 12:55.166
That bathroom
really needs a cleaning

12:55.233 --> 12:56.866
after the meeting,
it's a mess.

12:56.933 --> 12:59.233
Did you see how she lookedr
at me, when she said that?

13:00.333 --> 13:02.033
I must be changing.

13:02.100 --> 13:03.500
It's the virus.

13:03.566 --> 13:06.100
- I've gotta get out of here.
- What's going on here?

13:06.166 --> 13:07.233
It must be indigestion.

13:07.300 --> 13:08.633
Mary Beth
you are not turning

13:08.700 --> 13:10.000
into a cleaning woman.

13:10.066 --> 13:11.833
You're the same old..

13:11.900 --> 13:13.466
Uh, same old..

13:13.533 --> 13:15.500
Princess, you always were.

13:19.133 --> 13:20.966
- Are you Ginger Morgan?
- No!

13:21.033 --> 13:24.233
Take her. She went back
for seconds and had dessert.

13:24.300 --> 13:26.066
Well, it's true
she's eats like a horse.

13:26.133 --> 13:28.100
Oh, look at that figure,
it's not natural.

13:28.166 --> 13:31.233
I barely picked up my food.
I should be okay.

13:31.300 --> 13:33.100
Best to remain inside
until we determine

13:33.166 --> 13:34.600
the extent of contamination.

13:34.666 --> 13:35.966
Contamination?

13:36.033 --> 13:37.733
Got a hot one.

13:41.233 --> 13:43.166
Don't worry.
We're professionals.

13:43.233 --> 13:45.233
- We're here to help.
- Tag her.

13:47.633 --> 13:49.266
Tag them all.

13:49.333 --> 13:50.766
Neutralize the contact radius.

13:50.833 --> 13:54.300
And order up a 917 directive
when we're gone.

13:54.366 --> 13:55.966
You mind telling us,
what's going on here?

13:56.033 --> 13:58.466
Now, if you'll just
step into these.

13:58.533 --> 13:59.900
What are these?

13:59.966 --> 14:02.800
We're gonna transport you in
order to contain the exposure.

14:02.866 --> 14:05.366
Oh, those are body bags.

14:05.433 --> 14:07.166
Now, we're on a low budget.

14:07.233 --> 14:10.000
Um, I-I think
we'll just stay here.

14:10.066 --> 14:12.766
Yeah, we feel fine.
Really.

14:12.833 --> 14:13.766
Body bags?

14:13.833 --> 14:15.933
Huh? As in dead bodies?

14:16.000 --> 14:17.066
What do you wanna think about?

14:19.366 --> 14:22.366
I suggest a 604 insertion.

14:22.433 --> 14:24.400
For once. I concur.

14:35.900 --> 14:37.866
Dr. Picard,
you're new to our team.

14:37.933 --> 14:40.800
I suggest you put in
for more suit training.

14:40.866 --> 14:43.400
You're not fully mobile yet,
let's bag them.

14:56.733 --> 14:59.666
I'm Dr. Henry Picard,
project psychologist.

14:59.733 --> 15:01.966
You've already met
Dr. Clayton Van Der Straten.

15:02.033 --> 15:03.800
'Our project director.'

15:03.866 --> 15:05.966
'Dr. Katherine Rostinskya.'

15:06.033 --> 15:07.533
'Chief bio chemist.'

15:15.466 --> 15:18.600
Um, what's going on here?
Where, where are we?

15:18.666 --> 15:19.733
You feel okay?

15:19.800 --> 15:21.200
A little imbalanced.

15:21.266 --> 15:22.600
It'll wear off quickly.

15:22.666 --> 15:25.366
You were sprayed with
a harmless nerve neutralizer.

15:25.433 --> 15:26.833
Do you have a mirror?

15:26.900 --> 15:28.566
Nothing's done
with mirrors here, ma'am.

15:28.633 --> 15:30.700
This complex is called Hazmat.

15:30.766 --> 15:33.100
Short for hazardous material.

15:33.166 --> 15:34.466
It's a bio medically pure lab

15:34.533 --> 15:37.266
designed to handle
environmental crisis.

15:37.333 --> 15:38.566
You're still in Springwood.

15:38.633 --> 15:40.433
Actually under Springwood.

15:40.500 --> 15:42.700
Five levels down.

15:42.766 --> 15:45.200
I wanna know where
we are staying.

15:45.266 --> 15:47.300
I, I'd like to freshen up.

15:47.366 --> 15:49.433
Because if we're
staying overnight

15:49.500 --> 15:52.833
I need a firm mattress
and some extra pillows.

15:52.900 --> 15:55.733
And, oh, I don't want
those little tiny soap bars.

15:55.800 --> 15:57.300
Oh, another thing..

15:57.366 --> 15:59.366
..about the room service..

16:08.933 --> 16:10.900
What happens when we have
to go to the bathroom?

16:14.866 --> 16:16.800
That's disgusting.

16:22.933 --> 16:24.500
Hey!

16:24.566 --> 16:27.733
Hey! We have a right
to know what's going on here.

16:27.800 --> 16:29.066
Should we tell them?
I'm not sure.

16:29.133 --> 16:30.333
Well, I don't think we should
tell them everything.

16:30.400 --> 16:31.433
I think he is
as possible.

16:31.500 --> 16:32.533
Alright.

16:33.800 --> 16:34.900
Very well.

16:36.300 --> 16:38.666
The man you came in
contact with...

16:38.733 --> 16:41.633
was Lieutenant Colonel
John Garrett.

16:41.700 --> 16:44.933
'Mission commander of
the secret US space lab probe.'

16:45.000 --> 16:46.566
An astronaut?

16:46.633 --> 16:48.133
'Exactly.'

16:48.200 --> 16:49.400
- You mean we--
- Mary Beth.

16:49.466 --> 16:51.633
Mary Beth.

16:51.700 --> 16:55.266
'The gentleman on your left,
is Captain R.D.Thomas.'

16:55.333 --> 16:57.600
'A renowned rocket scientist..'

16:57.666 --> 16:59.400
'...and chief mission pilot.'

16:59.466 --> 17:02.066
He's currently receiving
our best treatment.

17:02.133 --> 17:05.566
The entire space lab probe crew
was exposed to asteroid dust

17:05.633 --> 17:08.500
that carried an unknown
crystalline space dust

17:08.566 --> 17:12.100
'that appears to be
