36:51.433 --> 36:53.066
'You said left.'

36:59.966 --> 37:01.166
Oh!

37:01.233 --> 37:02.233
- Damn it!
- Oh!

37:07.833 --> 37:09.233
'Oliver?'

37:09.300 --> 37:11.033
'Yeah.'

37:11.100 --> 37:13.733
Don't we risk contamination
through those air ducts?

37:13.800 --> 37:17.400
Um...no,
they don't go anywhere.

37:17.466 --> 37:19.066
'They're designed
to prevent any living thing'

37:19.133 --> 37:22.066
from coming in
or, uh...going out.

37:29.066 --> 37:31.200
To the imminent
completion of our project.

37:31.266 --> 37:33.466
- Mm-hmm.
- Here, here.

37:33.533 --> 37:35.233
Let's hope it's soon.

37:46.833 --> 37:49.100
You really went through
with it, didn't you?

37:49.166 --> 37:51.233
You put the organism
in my drink.

37:51.300 --> 37:54.300
I'm sorry, Dr. Picard,
but we needed another subject.

37:54.366 --> 37:57.733
Well, look at it this way, you
may survive like the woman has.

37:57.800 --> 38:00.200
Or turn into
a pile of blue dust.

38:00.266 --> 38:01.600
That's a possibility.

38:01.666 --> 38:02.900
But look at it this way.

38:02.966 --> 38:04.933
You will have died
for your country.

38:06.366 --> 38:08.000
I've got to get outta here

